//! REAL external accept-KAT fixture — **Robinhood Chain testnet** (chain id 46630,
//! an EVM Arbitrum-Orbit L2 for tokenized stocks/RWA), captured via the live public RPC
//! `https://rpc.testnet.chain.robinhood.com` `eth_getProof` at a recent block. This is a
//! genuine EIP-1186 proof chain for a tokenized-stock (**TSLA — Tesla**) holding, NOT a
//! round-trip construction.
//!
//! Holder `0x8b251ADF19a78C6f9e9217E07CD3468C40F00343` (funded by the testnet faucet with
//! ETH + five tokenized stocks: PLTR, NFLX, AMZN, AMD, TSLA — 5.0 of each). This fixture
//! proves the **TSLA** holding (contract `0xc9f9…3bd4e`, `balanceOf` = 5e18 = 5.0 TSLA).
//!
//! The token uses OpenZeppelin v5 **ERC-7201 namespaced storage** — the `_balances`
//! mapping base slot is the 32-byte `openzeppelin.storage.ERC20` namespace
//! `0x52c6…bace00` (NOT a small `u64` slot), so the balance-slot key is computed with
//! `erc20_balance_slot_key_wide` and verified with `verify_erc20_holding_wide`.
//!
//! Regenerate: `cast rpc eth_getProof <TOKEN> [<SLOT_KEY>] <block>` against the Robinhood
//! testnet RPC, then the scratchpad fixture generator.

